        <updateDate>2024-06-24T19:38:27Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Improving Mental Health and Drug Treatment Act of 2023&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill permanently allows state Medicaid programs to receive federal payment for substance-use disorder services that are provided at institutions for mental diseases (IMDs) for individuals aged 21 to 64. The bill also extends the maximum length of stay over a 12-month period from 30 days to 45 days and requires state Medicaid programs to review IMD compliance with relevant standards of care.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
